trend_summary: Compact grid of row-houses remains dominant. Change is mainly infill: small vacant lots gain apartments, a few warehouses convert to lighter commercial uses, sports facilities are refurbished, and street/yard tree cover expands. No expansion into the adjacent woodland occurs; built-up fabric stays continuous and densely urban.
notable_changes: Several scattered empty parcels are built out with mid-rise residential blocks.
Older flat-roof industrial buildings east-central are replaced or reroofed for commercial use.
Running track and adjacent courts are resurfaced and slightly reconfigured.
